From Soup: 56 The Cartesian coordinates of the tether are determined with a simple build-up procedure that starts with the approximate coordinates of three successive sugar atoms (C2′, C3′, O3′) generated in the reconstruction of DNA from base-pair-step parameters. 25,26 Given these coordinates ( v n –2 , v n –1 , v n ), the spatial position v n +1 of a fourth atom n +1 can be determined from knowledge of (i) the length b of the chemical bond that joins atom n to atom n +1, (ii) the magnitude of the valence angle θ formed by atoms n –1, n , and n +1, and (iii) the value of the dihedral angle ϕ described by atoms n –2, n –1, n , and n +1.
