From Soup: 148 The local moves of the tether also include fluctuations, consistent with experiment, 8 in the virtual distance b S–Au between the sulfur atoms on the tether and the centers of the gold nanocrystals. We assume the stretching energy to be quadratic and assign an elastic constant k b equal to ( kT /2)〈 δb 2 S–Au 〉 −1 , where 〈 δb 2 S–Au 〉 1/2 is the observed root-mean-square deviation in the virtual-bond distance, k the Boltzmann constant, and T the temperature in Kelvin.
