From Soup: 157 We apply two different models of DNA deformability: the first an ideal, inextensible, twisted wormlike chain with the intrinsic structure and elastic parameters described in Methods and the second a naturally straight, mixed-sequence chain subject to the fluctuations in base-pair steps seen in high-resolution structures and scaled to yield a persistence length of ∼500 Å. 13,14
